headline.main: Japanese Submarines Attacking 'In Force' to East of Australia; JAPANESE LAUNCH SUBMARINE ATTACK

lead_paragraph: ALLIED HEADQUARTERS IN AUSTRALIA, Saturday, May 1 -- The Japanese have opened a submarine attack in force to the east of Australia, the High Command reported today.
abstract: Jap submarines reptd attacking US supply lines in force, east of Australia; Allied scout bomber attacks Jap cargo ship near Kavieng, New Ireland; Allied planes raid Gasmata and Cape Gloucester airdromes, Mubo area and Lae
